description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an exciting Team Leader role then look no further you have found it!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;78 Crawley Rd is a unique service within SPFT which is part of the Rehabilitation Hub but sits within the management of the Forensic CDS. As a Team Leader in this service you will be able to contribute to ongoing service development, be part of the leadership team and help to ensure the maintenance of high clinical standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Team leader the role carries a strong element of managerial responsibilities including liaison with Human Resource colleagues, sickness management and effective Health Roster management. You will be working alongside the Modern Matron and Clinical Nurse Specialist in developing the service and ensure the team are delivering care to the highest standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As service we have a strong commitment to delivering supervision to all staff and we strive to ensure that all appraisals are completed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal viewings are highly recommended for you to be able to see our excellent facilities in which we aim to provide the highest standards of inpatient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kevin Macey (Matron) 0300 304 3830 or Karen Friel (General Manager) 07388227404&lt;/p&gt;
